From: Yong Gan <yong.gan@nxp.com>
Date: Fri, 2 Jun 2017 09:20:55 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1825/5242] arm64: imx8: Fix drm_addmap_core fail for aarch64

commit  7b550009d0da8b8fd6bd37143a87a9e8c649e960 from
https://source.codeaurora.org/external/imx/linux-imx.git

Fix error on mapping fb in exa driver starting.

Signed-off-by: Yong Gan <yong.gan@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_bufs.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_bufs.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_bufs.c
index e2f775d..0890450 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_bufs.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_bufs.c
@@ -179,7 +179,7 @@ static int drm_addmap_core(struct drm_device *dev, resource_size_t offset,
 	switch (map->type) {
 	case _DRM_REGISTERS:
 	case _DRM_FRAME_BUFFER:
-#if !defined(__sparc__) && !defined(__alpha__) && !defined(__ia64__) && !defined(__powerpc64__) && !defined(__x86_64__) && !defined(__arm__)
+#if !defined(__sparc__) && !defined(__alpha__) && !defined(__ia64__) && !defined(__powerpc64__) && !defined(__x86_64__) && !defined(__arm__) && !defined(__aarch64__)
 		if (map->offset + (map->size-1) < map->offset ||
 		    map->offset < virt_to_phys(high_memory)) {
 			kfree(map);
